node.text:
The new BUGATTI smartwatch range, created with VIITA Watches, mirrors the unrivalled precision, artistry and technology synonymous with hyper sports cars crafted in Molsheim. Each of the models offers an innumerable amount of technical features and is built by hand with meticulous attention to detail for a seamless integration of more than 1,000 individual parts. Discover the collection at www.bugatti.com or www.bugatti-smartwatches.com. @bugatti_smartwatches

#BUGATTI #BUGATTILifestyle #BUGATTISmartwatches #VIITA #VIITAforBUGATTI #VIITAWatches

node.text: No other driver spends more time in a BUGATTI CHIRON than he does: Andy Wallace. In the last few years, the Englishman and Pilote Officiel covered a total of over 150,000 km in the hyper sports cars from Molsheim. He thus is the perfect person to show owners and fans how to make the most of this unique vehicle. In a series of five video clips, Andy explains the car’s technical details in a comprehensible manner and reveals what the CHIRON is capable of and still driving it safely. Fasten your seatbelts! #BUGATTI #Chiron #AndyWallace

node.text: No other driver spends more time in a BUGATTI CHIRON than he does: Andy Wallace. 30 years ago, the foundations for the modern hyper sports car were laid, with the reveal of the BUGATTI EB 110. Powered by a V12 engine with four turbochargers, utilising four-wheel-drive and two differentials, and built upon a production-car-first ultra-lightweight carbon monocoque, the EB 110 was entirely in a league of its own. In 1991, this technical composition was a sensation,  unlocking never-before-seen levels of roadgoing performance. 

This weekend, @bugattiautomobilicampogalliano will pay homage to this pioneer with the celebration of 30 Years of EB110 at the Fabbrica Blu in Campogalliano.

#BUGATTI #EB110 #VEYRON #30YearsEB110

node.text:
Today, we celebrate the 140th birthday of our founder, Ettore BUGATTI, a revolutionary designer and engineer who changed the course of automotive and motor racing history with his creations. In homage to the genius that established our company’s DNA over more than 110 years ago, our design department has created this unique artwork showcasing one of BUGATTI’s earliest game-changing racing creations with its latest; Type 35 and BOLIDE, finished in Ettore’s favourite colours of yellow and black.

From a young age, Ettore’s  ideas and inventions were not only original, but truly game radical. The very first BUGATTI, the Type 10 or “Pur Sang”, went against the grain in the name of lightness and size. Two years later, a modified Type 10 – known as the Type 13 – would see Ettore enter his first race at the French Grand Prix of 1911, tackling cars twice as heavy with engines three times as large. 
 
From then on, the rest is history. Ettore’s desire to craft ever-faster and more powerful machines saw the first Type 35 – the most successful racing car ever made – win over 2000 races. Such was his genius that he could not only develop lightweight racing cars but also the most luxurious car of its time: the 3.5-tonne Type 41 ‘Royale’, powered by a 12.8-liter engine of Ettore’s design.
 
By this time, Ettore had established BUGATTI as the pinnacle of automotive engineering and design – a position our marque holds to this very day more than 110 years later.

#BUGATTI #BUGATTIBolide #BOLIDE #Type35 #EttoreBugatti #ViveLaMarque

September is a special month for all Bugattisti, especially in Molsheim where the passionate spirit for the brand is almost tangible, as it was the Alsatian town, where company founder Ettore Bugatti decided to settle 112 years ago and set up his manufacture.
 
It is where @ebalsace celebrate each year his birthday on September 15 with a variety of events. The most opulent is the Festival BUGATTI to which the enthusiasts brought more than 70 BUGATTIs from all over Europe to parade in them through the city centre of Molsheim over the past weekend – honoring the mastermind, Ettore Bugatti.
 
Last but not least BUGATTI presented its most agile CHIRON, the Pur Sport, to modern era BUGATTI enthusiasts in a lap of honor at the @500Nocturnes at Anneau du Rhin, where more than 20 super sports cars competed in a four hour endurance race.

#BUGATTI #BUGATTIChiron #EttoreBugatti #Alsace #Molsheim #500Nocturnes #EnthousiastesBugattiAlsace #ViveLaMarque

The VEYRON is already an ultra-rare hyper sports car, yet there are even more exclusive editions of this tour de force in existence. 
 
2009 was a truly special year for BUGATTI, as the marque celebrated its 100th anniversary. To honour the occasion, four limited edition VEYRONs were revealed at the Concorso d’Eleganza Villa d’Este, Italy, recalling the prestigious racing history of the luxury brand and paying tribute to the most successful racing car of all time - the BUGATTI Type 35.
 
The four VEYRONs were presented in the racing colors of the countries that competed in motorsports at that time: blue for France, red for Italy, green for Britain and white for Germany.
 
Picture here is the one-of-one white VEYRON 16.4 Centenaire edition, named “Hermann zu Leiningen”, representing Germany. 

#VEYRON #Centenaire #VilladEste #HermannzuLeiningen

The BUGATTI Type 35 is recognized as the most successful racing car of all time, winning around 2,000 races in its various forms. Yet in 1926, a particularly special edition of the Type 35 was born: the BUGATTI ‘Baby’. As a half-scale Type 35, the BUGATTI ‘Baby’ was built by Ettore and Jean Bugatti for Ettore’s youngest son, Roland. The ‘Baby’ even went into full production until 1936.

To celebrate the 110th anniversary of BUGATTI in 2019, 500 examples of the ‘Baby II’ began to be crafted by @little.cars, recreating the exhilarating experience of driving a BUGATTI in miniature form. These small-scale, fully electric masterpieces are every bit as detailed and engineered as their full-scale siblings.

 #BUGATTI #Type35 #LittleCarCompany

The @jacobandco Bugatti Chiron Sapphire Crystal is the result of two years of research and development, and several months of materials processing, high level machining and hand polishing to produce a case with an unparalleled view of the 578 hand-decorated and hand-assembled components of the exclusive JCAM37 manual wound caliber. Sapphire is one of the hardest natural materials in the world, only eclipsed by diamond. Because of this diamond-tools are required to craft the case. Polishing is the most difficult and time consuming process taking a craftsman approximately 120 hours to complete the case by hand. This same delicate hand polishing is used for the caseback, the top, the three crowns and other pieces that are attached to the case. The result is a unique piece that fully exposes the groundbreaking totally functional replica of the BUGATTI W16 engine with its pistons pumping, turbochargers spinning as well as the whirl of the one-minute tourbillon.

#BUGATTI #BUGATTIChiron #JacobandCo #JacobandCoWatches #hautehorlogerie
